headline: Baltimore Daughter Says Squatters Took Over Her Sick Dad's Home, Ripped Out The Toilet, Set It On Fire, Got It Condemned — And Now They're Back Again
summary: If there were an award for "Most Relentless House in America," this burnt‑out, condemned Baltimore property would be a top contender. Vacant. Damaged. Set on fire. Invaded. Evicted. And through it all, somehow still attracting new "residents" like a moth...

headline: DC judge delivers smackdown to Airbnb squatter after ruling she has no tenancy. Homeowner rights finally defended?
summary: Rochanne Douglas's nightmare began when Romero booked her furnished home through Airbnb, claiming her own apartment had been damaged in a fire. Here's what Douglas didn't know.

headline: Gen Z is rebelling against the economy with ‘disillusionomics,’ tackling near 6-figure debt by turning life into a giant list of income streams
summary: Failed promises are reshaping how Gen Z approaches financial decisions and their role in the economy. Call it “disillusionomics,” Alice Lassman says.
